Package: iextend-evdi-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends:
  dkms,
  make,
  gcc,
  linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers,
  ${misc:Depends}
Recommends:
  mokutil,
  sbsigntool
Description: iExtend virtual display driver (evdi DKMS module)
 Provides the evdi kernel module (maintained by DisplayLink, GPL-2.0)
 as a DKMS source package.  After installation, DKMS builds and installs
 the module for the currently running kernel and any future kernel upgrades.
 .
 On SecureBoot systems the postinst script generates a machine-unique
 signing certificate and prints a mokutil command to enroll it.
 .
 This package is intentionally separate from the Apache-2.0 iextend
 daemon: iextend loads libevdi at runtime via dlopen, keeping its own
 license unaffected by evdi's GPL.
